Markiya Dickson was shot and killed at Fonticello Park (formerly Carter Jones Park) at a cookout in May 2019. She was a student at Chesterfield’s Crestwood Elementary and was previously a student at Redd Elementary in Richmond. She was only 9 years old, this post is for HER. 

Today we (@forthefeminyou) witnessed the ribbon cutting to an imagination zone named in her honor at the Park where this tragedy took place. We activated a children's sip'n paint led by @ease_thearchitect of @alleviativeproductions and gave away children's books from "THE BOOK LADY - Khadijah Mahdi. It was so rewarding to connect with the youth and witness their creativity and love for Art. They enjoyed their tasty snacks & drinks and truly had a blast. The blue raspberry scoops from @rubyscoopsic were nostalgic and activated my inner child today. Huge love to Markiyas family for initiating this labor of love amidst unimaginable pain. Thank you @fonticelloparkrva
For having us!

1. DJ EXXO - "As a timid soul she began writing poetry at the age of 12 and eventually transitioned to drama and media entertainment; as the stage became a safe space for her. Music was always a love but didn’t become the star of her life until she started her sophomore year at vcu. While attending, she encountered an opportunity to expand on her love and began researching the art of djing."....

2. DJ EASE - "Ease is an activist for human and nature rights. 
Ease has produced an abundance of mixed media for over 30 years.  Ease implements anthropology, history, and spiritualism within their designs. 
Ease is the founder and operator of Alleviative Productions, a mixed media production company based in Richmond, VA. Ease is an open format DJ who curates setlists based upon their audience and environment. "

3. DJ L.O.E - "Born and raised in Newport News, VA, now residing in Richmond, Lauren has been in music in some way since a child whether that be the church choir or dance team. Growing up in the church, gospel music influences were abundant: Kirk Franklin, Mary Mary, Fred Hammond, etc. One thing Lauren grasped from those classic gospel records was the beat, the energy, the essence of the soulful drums and synths. It stuck with her and became the foundation for her love of music."

4. AKA$HA - "Growing up in a musical household, Aka$ha was surrounded by a rich tapestry of influences that shaped her love for music. Inspired by iconic artists such as Aaliyah, Sade, Jay-Z, OutKast, Pharrell, Frank Ocean, Eve, and Foxy Brown, she developed a diverse musical palette. Aka$ha's upbringing, combined with her own experiences, served as the foundation for her nostalgic yet futuristic style."

5. CHARNELLE - Charnelle has been recording music since the age of 13, has since released a couple of projects, many music videos, and quite a few singles. Performed at many different festivals, birthday parties, as well as small venues.

Years back I was alienated from this community after a black woman I trusted told everyone I lied about being raped by a popular musician that played there. Citing I "lied for attention". Ladies and gentlemen this is called RAPE CULTURE. 

The level of healing that had to take place was IMMENSE. 3 years in Miami....a few years in Brooklyn and a few years in LA. Being back in my hometown has taken the band-aid off, but I have RENEWED skin. I'm no longer being quiet about the white supremacy that has plagued us here in Richmond Virginia. Our proximity to whiteness has caused so much damage in the BIPOC community. The lists I've provided are based on MY and other folks experiences that I KNOW personally. Please don't ever be silent about terrible experiences you have with businesses/entities/communities/organizations.... it helps NO ONE if you're silent.

I know creatives are struggling with exactly what to say or do with the world in absolute shambles. The desensitization started a long time ago in our own hoods, but has now reached new heights. Take a moment away if need be.  Pour into your mental and spiritual needs right now. You ARE doing ALL that you can do.
